%p.project__para The panels for all of the first run MFOS modules was machined from 6061 aluminium on a small Shapeoko 2 CNC machine. The vector files for CNC machining and engraving were created in Adobe Illustrator, and CAM files were prepared in CAMBAM.

%p.project__para

%p.project__para The graffiti text artwork for the VCOs was done by my friend Travis G Dale, which was then scanned and converted to vectors for engraving. The panel artwork for the LFO module was created procedurally using the Processing graphics programming environment. The panel artwork for the VCF is based on Felix the Cat LSD blotter sheets.

